Name: Male
Description: Malé (މާލ), pronounced Mah-lay, is the capital of Maldives.  The city occupies the entire islet of Malé and is located at the southern rim of North Male Atoll.

Name: Seenu
Description: Addu (also Seenu) is the southernmost atoll in the Maldives.  Hithadhoo, its capital, was the base of the short-lived United Suvadive Republic secessionist movement in 1959–1963.

Name: Kuredu
Description: Kuredu (Kurendhoo) is an island located in the Lhaviyani Atoll of the Maldives.

Name: Mathiveri
Description: Mathiveri is a small island that belongs to North Ari atoll, Maldives. Only 900 citizens live there.

Name: Rasdhoo
Description: Rasdhoo is a smallish island with 850 citizens and a capital of Alif Alif Atoll (or North Ari Atoll), Maldives.

Name: Thoddoo
Description: Thoddoo is an isolated inhabited island that administratively belongs to North Ari atoll, Maldives. It's quite large by Maldivian standards, it will take about an hour to circumvent it.

Name: Ukulhas
Description: Ukulhas (Dhivehi: އުކުޅަސް) island is one of the inhabited islands of North Ari Atoll in the Maldives. The island has been a travel destination since 2012; therefore, it has just a couple of inns and is somewhat hard to get to. Hence, if you enjoy diving, fishing and swimming without a crowd of fellow tourists, Ukulhas might be the destination you're looking for.
